definition.value: A member of the class of p-quinones resulting from the formal oxidation of the hydroquinone moiety of 5,7,8-trihydroxy-6-methoxy-2H-chromen-2-one.
A uridine 5'-phosphate that is the 5,6-dihydro derivative of uridine 5'-monophosphate; major microspecies at pH 7.3
Any member of the class of 8-methylmenaquinones that is 2,8-dimethyl-1,4-naphthoquinone with an unsaturated isoprenoid chain at the 3-position.
A member of the class of prenylnapthoquinones that carries a methyl group at position 5.
An alkyl-gibberellin that is gibberellin A4 carrying an extra methyl substituent at position 1beta (4beta using gibbane skeletal numbering).
A diterpenoid that is a C19 gibberellin alkylated at position 1 or 2 (position 4 or 3 respectively using gibbane skeletal numbering).
An alkyl-gibberellin that is gibberellin A4 carrying an extra methyl substituent at position 1alpha (4alpha using gibbane skeletal numbering).
An alkyl-gibberellin that is gibberellin A4 carrying an extra methyl substituent at position 2beta (3beta using gibbane skeletal numbering).
An alkyl-gibberellin that is gibberellin A4 carrying an extra methyl substituent at position 2alpha (3alpha using gibbane skeletal numbering).
An alkyl-gibberellin that is gibberellin A1 carrying an extra methyl substituent at position 2beta (3beta using gibbane skeletal numbering).
Any organic heterotricyclic compound that is any benzodiazepine which is ortho-fused with a imidazole.
An alkyl-gibberellin that is gibberellin A1 carrying an extra methyl substituent at position 2alpha (3alpha using gibbane skeletal numbering).
A halo-gibberellin that is gibberellin A9 carrying a chloro substituent at position 3beta (2beta using gibbane skeletal numbering).
A diterpenoid that is a C19 gibberellin halogenated commonly at position 3 (position 2 using gibbane skeletal numbering).
A halo-gibberellin that is gibberellin A9 carrying a fluoro substituent at position 3beta (2beta using gibbane skeletal numbering).
A diterpenoid that is a derivative of a gibberellin in which only one of the stereogenic centres differs in configuration from the parent compound.
An epi-gibberellin that is gibberellin A1 differing in configuration at C-3 (C-2 using gibbane skeletal numbering).
An epi-gibberellin that is gibberellin A4 differing in configuration at C-3 (C-2 using gibbane skeletal numbering).
A beta-D-glucoside resulting from the formal condensation of the phenolic hydroxy group of (E)-sinapaldehyde with beta-D-glucose.
A nitro compound obtained by the formal condensation of prostaglandin E2 with 1,3-dinitroglycerol.
A synthetic dipyrrin derived from rings A and D of bilirubin IXalpha in which C-9 carries a phenyldiazenyl substituent.

A polysaccharide derivative with a repeating unit consisting of alpha-D-mannosyl, alpha-L-rhamnosyl (acetylated on either O-2 or -3) and alpha-D-galactosyl residues linked sequentially (1->4) and (1->3), to the mannosyl residue is linked (1->3) an alpha-abequosyl residue (partially acetylated on O-2), while to the galactosyl residue is linked (1->4) or (1->6) an alpha-D-glucosyl residue, with all repeating units being linked (1->2). O-polysaccharide repeat from Salmonella Typhimurium (serogroup B).

A polysaccharide derivative with a repeating unit consisting of alpha-D-mannosyl, alpha-L-rhamnosyl and alpha-D-galactosyl residues linked sequentially (1->4) and (1->3), to the mannosyl residue is linked (1->3) an alpha-tivelosyl residue, while to the galactosyl residue is linked (1->4) or (1->6) an alpha-D-glucosyl residue, with all repeating units being linked (1->2). O-polysaccharide repeat from Salmonella Enteritidis (serogroup D).
A synthetic dipyrrin derived from rings A and D of bilirubin IXalpha in which C-9 carries a 2-[2-(ethoxycarbonyl)phenyl]diazenyl substituent.
A synthetic dipyrrin derived from rings A and D of bilirubin IXalpha in which C-9 carries a 2-(4-sulfophenyl)diazenyl substituent.

A member of the class of octahydronaphthalenes that is (2R,4aS,5R,6R,8aS)-2,5-dimethyl-6-[(1E)-prop-1-en-1-yl]-1,2,3,4,4a,5,6,8a-octahydronaphthalene in which the hydrogen at position 5 has been replaced by a (Z)-hydroxy[(5S)-5-(hydroxymethyl)-2,4-dioxopyrrolidin-3-ylidene]methyl group. Produced by the dual culture of Trichoderma harzianum and Catharanthus roseus callus, it exhibits significant antimicrobial activity against Gram-positive bacteria such as Staphylococcus aureus and Bacillus subtilis.
A hydrazone that is a tautomer of 8-(2-carboxyethyl)-2,7-dimethyl-3-vinyl-9-(phenyldiazenyl)dipyrrin-1(10H)-one.

A member of the class of tetramic acids that is trichosetin in which the hydrogen attached to the lactam nitrogen has been replaced by a methyl group. It is produced by the filamentous fungus Fusarium heterosporum.
A biladiene that is a linear tetrapyrrole and a regioisomer of bilirubin IXalpha, in which the dipyrroles are of exovinyl type only.
A biladiene that is a linear tetrapyrrole and a regioisomer of bilirubin IXalpha, in which the dipyrroles are of endovinyl type only.
A member of the class of hydroxyindoles that is 1H-indol-4-ol which is substituted by a nitriloacetyl group at the 3 position.
A member of the class of indoles that is 1H-indole which is substituted by a nitriloacetyl group at the 3 position.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from N(4)-(alpha-D-glucan)-L-asparagine, in which the glucose units are connected by (1->6) linkages.
